OL,3,CEuston station's marble columns 'would
OL,4,Cfall off' without bands, minister
OL,5,Cadmits
OL,7,FEuston Station in central London has
OL,8,Fdeteriorated to the point where its
OL,9,Fmarble columns are held together by
OL,10,Fbands because "it would fall off
OL,11,Fwithout them", the rail minister has
OL,12,Fsaid.
OL,14,FLord Hendy of Richmond Hill, who is a
OL,15,Fformer chairman of Network Rail, told
OL,16,Fthe House of Lords that Euston
OL,17,FStation, one of Britain's busiest, is
OL,18,F"no longer in fit condition".
